question.en:
Consider the Repository Pattern and Dependency Inversion Principle working together:

typescript
// Without proper DI
class OrderService {
  private repo = new MySqlOrderRepository();
  async getOrder(id: string) {
    return this.repo.findById(id);
  }
}

// With DI and Repository Pattern
interface IOrderRepository {
  findById(id: string): Promise<Order>;
}

class OrderService {
  constructor(private repo: IOrderRepository) {}
  async getOrder(id: string) {
    return this.repo.findById(id);
  }
}


Why is the second approach considered better for an enterprise application?

